Mediacorp Logo Mediacorp is a state-funded media conglomorate in Singapore. Owned by Temasek Holdings, a state-owned investment company, it operates television, radio, and digital properties. It holds a monopoly on terrestrial television in the country, operating six channels in Singapore’s four official languages of Malay, English, Mandarin Chinese, and Tamil. Source
